WEBVTT

0
00:00:00.330 --> 00:00:01.090
In this scenario,

1
00:00:01.169 --> 00:00:04.650
we are working an Incident which has recurred several times over the last month.

2
00:00:06.590 --> 00:00:08.189
The root cause remains unknown.

3
00:00:09.819 --> 00:00:13.449
But we can see from previous occurrences that there is an established workaround

4
00:00:13.619 --> 00:00:16.479
that has been successfully used in the past to restore service.

5
00:00:16.979 --> 00:00:18.239
Once we've applied the workaround,

6
00:00:18.569 --> 00:00:20.979
we can copy the Resolution Notes from the previous Incident.

7
00:00:23.149 --> 00:00:23.329
Now,

8
00:00:23.430 --> 00:00:24.750
let's proceed to resolve the ticket.

9
00:00:26.469 --> 00:00:28.629
We'll select the appropriate Resolution Code,

10
00:00:28.829 --> 00:00:30.149
Resolved (with workaround).

11
00:00:30.899 --> 00:00:32.580
Adjust the Resolution Notes if needed,

12
00:00:32.729 --> 00:00:33.840
then click Resolve.

13
00:00:35.349 --> 00:00:35.650
Now,

14
00:00:35.830 --> 00:00:37.250
let's create the Problem record.

15
00:00:37.750 --> 00:00:38.830
From the More Actions menu,

16
00:00:39.029 --> 00:00:40.209
choose Create Problem.

17
00:00:42.189 --> 00:00:43.500
A new Problem is created,

18
00:00:43.630 --> 00:00:46.110
pre-populated with data from the originating Incident.

19
00:00:49.020 --> 00:00:50.669
You can make changes if needed

20
00:00:50.869 --> 00:00:53.169
to the Short Description and Description fields,

21
00:00:53.419 --> 00:00:54.979
as well as any other fields,

22
00:00:55.349 --> 00:00:57.189
to provide a detailed summary of the

23
00:00:57.189 --> 00:00:59.750
issue and enable proper assessment and analysis.

24
00:01:01.020 --> 00:01:02.900
We saw earlier that there were other Incidents in

25
00:01:02.900 --> 00:01:05.190
the system for previous occurrences of this Problem.

26
00:01:05.809 --> 00:01:08.449
So let's head to the Related Records tab to relate them.

27
00:01:08.750 --> 00:01:09.510
As you can see,

28
00:01:09.580 --> 00:01:11.930
the originating Incident is already listed.

29
00:01:12.220 --> 00:01:13.500
To relate additional Incidents,

30
00:01:13.580 --> 00:01:14.180
click Add.

31
00:01:16.139 --> 00:01:19.059
Apply any filters needed to find the relevant Incidents,

32
00:01:19.500 --> 00:01:21.400
then use the checkboxes to select them,

33
00:01:21.699 --> 00:01:23.540
then click Add to relate them to the record.

34
00:01:25.680 --> 00:01:27.599
We're now ready to assign the Problem record

35
00:01:27.599 --> 00:01:29.720
to the Problem Management group for assessment.

36
00:01:30.900 --> 00:01:31.569
Click Assign.

37
00:01:33.449 --> 00:01:35.620
Select the Problem Management assignment group.

38
00:01:39.680 --> 00:01:40.959
Add Work Notes as needed.

39
00:01:44.760 --> 00:01:45.940
Then click Save

40
00:01:47.870 --> 00:01:48.559
That's it.

41
00:01:48.800 --> 00:01:50.489
The Problem is now assigned to the Problem

42
00:01:50.489 --> 00:01:53.080
Management group for assessment and further investigation.
